    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="100"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 21641/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Harvey</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 28.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The department has received your No. 9 of the 7th
                    instant, in regard to the extradition of Vahan Nalbandian, and commends your
                    manner of procedure in this case.</p>
                <p>You will convey to the Bulgarian foreign office an expression of this
                    department’s high appreciation of the very gracious and friendly action of the
                    Bulgarian Government in this matter.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
